description:
This is a 17 minute workout called 'Gradual Climb Row' from the channel Dani Hansen.
The workout falls under Cardio/Indoor rowing.
It's suitable for Intermediate fitness levels.
You'll need Rower for this workout.
The workout has a The Endorphin Wave and The Meditative Grind vibe.
The The Endorphin Wave vibe means Elevated energy, feel-good movement, steady build. This is especially good for When you want a challenging but steady burn. The The Meditative Grind vibe means Zone in, lock down, let repetition take over. This is especially good for Those who love a slow burn and rhythmic intensity..
The technique difficulty is Intermediate and Beginner.
The effort required is Moderate and Challenging.

Original workout description: Shift up in rhythm one beat each minute with Dani as you stay at a fast run pace. 

Max rhythm: 28, Format: Climb...
